# Knowledge Pipeline Fix — 4 Agent Prompts (SQLite + FTS5)
#
# Strict sequential: Prompt 1 → 2 → 3 → 4
#
# Estimated total: ~48K active tokens
# Based on: 181 agent calls, median 2097 output, P90 22710
#
# What this fixes (from .handoff.md audit):
#   #1 pending.md write-only         → Prompt 1 (migration) + Prompt 2 (write path)
#   #2 only 1/113 eval JSONs read    → Prompt 1 (migration) + Prompt 3 (read path)
#   #3 repo learnings never injected → Prompt 1 (migration) + Prompt 3 (FTS5 query)
#   #4 MistakeTracker volatile       → Prompt 2 (persistence + store writes)
#   #5 auto-QA findings dead         → Prompt 2 (writeback to store)
#
# Backtest methodology (Prompt 4):
#   For each sitdeck feature (37+), run the FTS5 query with the feature
#   name/spec as input. Compare returned learnings against what the eval
#   sidecar actually found for that feature (113 eval JSONs = ground truth).
#   Precision: what % of returned learnings relate to actual issues found.
#   Recall: what % of actual issues had a relevant learning returned.
#   Tune FTS5 column weights (title vs body vs tags) based on results.


===========================================================================
PROMPT 1 OF 4: Build the Knowledge Store + Migrate All Existing Data
Estimated: ~14K active tokens
===========================================================================

## Problem

No queryable knowledge store exists. 300+ learnings in flat markdown, 113 eval JSONs in a logs dir, 128 pending entries in a write-only file. Nothing is searchable or filterable by relevance.

## What to build

`py/auto_sdd/lib/knowledge_store.py` — SQLite database with FTS5 full-text search.

Schema: `learnings` table (id, title, body, tags, type, source, project, date, status, confidence) + `learnings_fts` virtual table on title/body/tags for BM25 ranking.

API: `init_store`, `insert_learning`, `query_relevant` (FTS5 MATCH + BM25 ORDER BY rank), `migrate_from_markdown` (parse all L-series + pending entries), `migrate_from_evals` (parse all eval JSONs), `get_store_path`.

## Where to find the answers

- `learnings/core.md` and `learnings/failure-patterns.md` — entry format: `## L-NNNNN — title` then Type:, Tags:, Confidence:, Status:, Date:, Related:, body text. Parse these.
- `learnings/pending.md` — entry format: `## [pending] CATEGORY — project / feature — date` then Timestamp:, Category:, Project:, Feature:, body. Parse these.
- `logs/compstak-sitdeck/evals/eval-*.json` — JSON with `mechanical` and `agent_eval` objects. Fields: framework_compliance, scope_assessment, integration_quality, repeated_mistakes, eval_notes.
- Python `sqlite3` stdlib — FTS5 is bundled with Python 3.9+.

## Scope

- Create: `py/auto_sdd/lib/knowledge_store.py`, `py/tests/test_knowledge_store.py`
- Modify: `Agents.md`
- No other files. No package managers. No push.


